definitions.definition: A hole formed in soluble rock by the action of water , serving to conduct surface water to an underground passage.
A depressed area in which waste or drainage collects.
A hole in the playfield that rewards the player when the ball is guided into it.
A domain name server that has been configured to hand out non-routeable addresses for all domains, so that every computer that uses it will fail to get access to the real website.
An attack which redirects requests , whether network or memory accesses , to a new location defined by the attacker .

main_definition: ( geology ) A hole formed in soluble rock by the action of water , serving to conduct surface water to an underground passage.
secondary_definitions: A depressed area in which waste or drainage collects.
( pinball ) A hole in the playfield that rewards the player when the ball is guided into it.
( Internet ) A domain name server that has been configured to hand out non-routeable addresses for all domains, so that every computer that uses it will fail to get access to the real website.
( computer security ) An attack which redirects requests , whether network or memory accesses , to a new location defined by the attacker .
